Reasoning: The paper deals with the performance analysis of relaying techniques for ultra-reliable short-packet communications, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of loop interference suppression, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY). The use of finite blocklength codes for short-packet communications is a topic related to communication theory (cs.COMM). Finally, the paper mentions the potential applications of the proposed techniques in multimedia communications (cs.MM).
